title: SWAT officers called to Northeast Austin apartment
content:
Please install the latest Adobe Flash Player Plugin to watch this content.
AUSTIN (KXAN) — SWAT officers responded to a Northeast Austin apartment Monday after a man refused to come out of his home, police said.
Police received a call about 1:20 p.m. from a man who said he was suicidal at the Mueller Flats apartments, 1071 Clayton Lane. SWAT officers arrived at the apartment complex about an hour later.
Austin police said the SWAT situation ended around 5:30 p.m. Police said the man in his mid-20’s committed suicide before SWAT arrived.
Austin ISD police said Harris Elementary School students who lived near the scene would be held at the school until the situation was resolved or until their parents picked them up.
